# Coding Specification

1.Identifiers:
----Class/Structure/Union name:
	1.Start with capital letter
	2.Each word's first letter must be capital letter
	3.No spaces or underlines between words
	Example:
		1.NFunctionDefinition
		2.ErrorMessage
		3.LValue

----Function/Method name:
	1.if the name only have one word(such as "create", "get"), this word must start with capital letter
	2.if the name have two or above words, the first word start with lower-case letter while the following words start with capital letter
	3.No spaces or underlines between words
	Example:
		1.doAssignCast
		2.Create
		3.getTypeId

----Field/Local variable name:
	1.all lower-case letter
	2.use underlines between words
	Example:
		1.ptr_dim
		2.value
		3.line_number
		4.lval

----Generic type name:
	1.all capital letter
	2.number 1 to n(if have more than one type)
	Example:
		1.T
		2.T1
		3.T2

Some specific abbreviations("opt" means this ab. only used in long name):
1.value 		-> val // opt
2.number 		-> num // opt
3.pointer 		-> ptr
4.array 		-> arr // opt
5.string 		-> str // opt
6.iterator 		-> it
7.line number 	-> lineno
8.function 		-> func
9.temp			-> tmp
10.argument		-> arg // opt
11.expression	-> expr
12.instruction	-> inst
13.element		-> elem // opt
14.return		-> ret
15.index		-> idx // opt
16.parameter	-> param
17.specifier	-> spec // opt
18.identifier	-> id // opt
